tobacco free campus Home UIC Campus Law Compliance Questions Employee Resources Tobacco Free Campus THE UIC CAMPUS The University of Illinois at Chicago is a tobacco free campus  The presence of tobacco products at UIC poses a health risk for everyone on campus   UIC has prohibited smoking indoors and near building entryways since       The Tobacco Free n    Campus Policy went into effect January          This policy was expanded the followinging year to n    comply with the Smoke Free Campus Act      ILCS          which required all campuses in n    Illinois to institute disciplinary action  fines  and an appeals process for violation of this n    policy The Tobacco Free Campus Policy applies to all forms of tobacco  including but not limited to n    cigarettes  cigars  pipes  water pipes  hookahs  chew  electronic cigarettes  and smokeless n    tobacco products LAW Beginning July          the State of Illinois mandated that smoking be prohibited on n        every campus of a state supported institution of higher education  This applies to each n        campus  including buildings  grounds  parking lots  and vehicles owned and operated by n        universities  employees  guests  and students Each state supported institution of higher education has the authority to implement the  n        act accordingly and authorize and distribute all policies and regulations necessary for  n        this purpose  This may include  but is not limited to  citations  fines  and disciplinary  n        action COMPLIANCE In compliance with the State of Illinois Smoke Free Campus Act      ILCS  n             additional "no smoking" signs have been posted around campus and all ashtrays have been  n    removed from university property  The UIC campus has instituted a system of citations and n    fines  The UIC Police Department now has the authority to issue citations and related fines n    for violations of the Tobacco Free Campus policy Fines are issued according to the following schedule   Individuals who observe someone smoking in a location prohibited by our policy should  n        contact the UIC Police at the non emergency number                Violations must be  n        reported at the time they occur  Staff and faculty violators will be reported to UIC Human n        Resources and or Faculty Affairs  Students in violation of the policy will be reported n        directly to the Dean of Student Affairs  Repeated violations by an individual may lead to n        disciplinary action QUESTIONS Why did our campus go smoke free  By eliminating second hand smoke  the Chicago campus underscores its commitment to providing n     a healthy learning environment for students and a healthy work environment for faculty and  n     staff Free Illinois Act      ILC  n         and complies with the Smoke Free Campus Act      ILCS          which required all  n    Illinois campuses to become smoke free as of July         When did the University of Illinois at Chicago become smoke free  The Smoke Free Campus Policy went into effect January         for the Chicago campus   On  t n    July         this policy was expanded to comply with the Smoke Free Campus Act      ILCS  n             which required all campuses in Illinois to institute disciplinary action  fines  and  n    an appeals process Are there designated smoking areas on campus  No  Smoking is prohibited on all campus property  Those choosing to smoke must do so at  n    least    feet from any property owned or controlled by the campus  Please consult the  n    Smoke Free Campus map at maps uic edu for more information about campus boundaries  n t maps uic edu What about basketball games  concerts or other public events  All events occurring on campus property are covered by the smoke free policy Can people smoke in their own vehicles within the smoke free campus What about in  t n    university vehicles  Yes  you are allowed to smoke in your private vehicles  Smoking in university vehicles has been prohibited for several years and remains so under this policy My citation says that my fine can be waived if I complete an online course  How do I do that  If you received your citation for a third violation of the Smoke Free Campus policy  you have the option of either paying the fine according to the instructions on the front of the citation or completing UIC s Nicotine     course here  This online course must be completed within    hours of the issuance of the citation here I am a student and I received a citation  What are my options  wellnesscenter uic edu smokefree index html  nStudent citations may also be referred to the Office of the Dean of Students for disciplinary action through the student conduct process  Students will be notified upon receipt of this smoking citation  Outcomes rendered in the student conduct process are independent of the prescribed consequences listed in this citation I am a staff faculty visitor and I received a citation   What are my options  wellnesscenter uic edu smokefree index html  nStaff and faculty citations may be referred to UIC Human Resources for disciplinary action  Staff faculty will be notified upon receipt of this smoking citation How can I appeal this citation  All student appeals must go through the Dean of Students Office by going to dos uic edu and all faculty staff appeals must go through Human Resources by going to www hr uic edu Appeals must be submitted within    calendar days of the violation date and the citation must be paid in full before you may file an official appeal  An appeals board made up of faculty  staff and students will review appeals and other relevant information in making a determination  The appeals board will notify the appellant of their decision within    business days  n dos uic edu www hr uic edu Who should I contact for additional information about the Illinois Smoke Free Campus Act   nUniversity of Illinois at Chicago  nPolice Department n    West Maxwell Street t nRm       M C      n